tourBios.curYearHigh: Earned exempt status in a playoff at the Florida Qualifying Tournament.
tourBios.carHigh: Has played on the Tar Heel Tour, the Hooters Tour and the Asian Tour. Most recently has spent time on the Canadian Tour, where he enjoyed a T42 at the 2010 Corona Mazatlan Mexico PGA Championship in his Tour debut.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Won the Pac-10 individual title as a senior in 2008.

tourBios.curYrHigh: Earned exempt status in a playoff at the Florida Qualifying Tournament.
tourBios.personal: Scored the winning goal in a shootout for Team PGA TOUR Canada in the 2012 playing of The Miracle On Grass, a grass hockey game against NHL players, including Chicago Blackhawk Jonathan Toews...Has aspirations of running for the U.S. Presidency in 2020...Is an avid outdoorsman and enjoys hunting and fishing
tourBios.prYrSeason:
2012: Made three cuts, finishing a season-best T8 at the Dakota Dunes Open.

2011: Made three cuts, finishing a season-best T8 at the TOUR Championship.

2010: Made the cut in his PGA TOUR Canada debut at the Corona Mazatlan Mexican PGA Championship, where he finished T42, Received non-exempt status for the season at the California Winter Qualifying School.
